HEADWORD: Noematachograph
<hw>No*e`ma*tach"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>no`hma</grk> the understanding + <grk>ta`chos</grk> swiftness +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for determining and
registering the duration of more or less complex operations of the
mind.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

